AntOS is known to work in linux x86 (gcc 4.4.5).

1. Download the AntOS source code;
2. Make sure you have gcc, g++ and make installed;
3. Make sure you have gdb if you want to debug;
4. Install LLVM 3.0 or higher;
5. mkdir AntOS/depend;
6. Download UTF-8 C++ library and place it into depend/utf8;
7. cd to AntOS/src and do make.
